  "body": "### Describe the feature\n\nWe officially accept js numbers, bigints, ethers's bignumbers and some other bignumber implementations. But strings kind of work, and users do use them, so we should:\r\n\r\n- Correctly handle them and add proper tests for them\r\n- Add an explanation about which kind of strings are accepted. I'd say we accept whatever can be casted to bigint with its constructor, so \"1\", \"0xA\", \"0o10\" and even \"0b1010\"\n\n### Search terms\n\nchai matchers strings to be equal numbers",
